  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> element itself has no accessibility implications - it's purely a mechanism for resource selection. Accessibility considerations apply to the parent elements:</p>

    <ul>
      <li><strong>Picture</strong>: Ensure the <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> has appropriate <code>alt</code> text</li>
      <li><strong>Video</strong>: Provide <a href="/docs/elements/native/track/"><code>&lt;track&gt;</code></a> elements for captions</li>
      <li><strong>Audio</strong>: Provide transcripts for audio content</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

